<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR MEATLESS GOOD FRIDAY; 
</P>
<P>
QUICK SPANISH COD PAN- BAKE IS SPICY ENTREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quick Spanish Cod Pan-Bake is fish prepared in a flavorful sauce with a cook's 
choice of vegetables and other ingredients, all baked together in a chunky 
green chile salsa or picante sauce. Served over a variety of hot cooked 
vegetables, this is a perfect dish to serve if the family is observing the 
meatless Good Friday tradition during the Easter season. 
</P>
<P>
QUICK SPANISH COD PAN-BAKE 
</P>
<P>
1 pound cod fillets 
</P>
<P>
Salt, pepper 
</P>
<P>
1/2 green pepper, cut into 1/4-inch strips 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons chopped shallots 
</P>
<P>
1 tablespoon olive oil 
</P>
<P>
1 cup mild green chile salsa or chunky picante sauce 
</P>
<P>
1/3 cup sliced pimiento-stuffed green olives 
</P>
<P>
1/2 teaspoon saffron 
</P>
<P>
Season cod to taste with salt and pepper. Arrange in shallow casserole. 
</P>
<P>
Saute green pepper and shallots in hot oil until tender. Stir in salsa, olives 
and saffron. Place cod in pan and spoon some of sauce over fish. 
</P>
<P>
Cover and bake at 450 degrees 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when 
tested with fork. Makes 2 servings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
