<P>
Photo, Cafe Peppered A drive-by rifleman blasted the window of a downtown 
restaurant about 2:45 a.m., but no one was injured, authorities said. The 
Denny's at 530 Ramirez St. was open for business at the time, but the few 
patrons ducked when the shooting started and no one saw the attacker. Police 
officials said about 10 rounds were fired from an assault rifle. Associated 
Press 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
