<P>
AFGHAN JETS BOMB REBELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Afghan jets bombed guerrilla positions around the strategic eastern city of 
Jalalabad, and Kabul radio said that hundreds of insurgents were killed in a 
failed attempt to capture the city. The guerrillas admitted that bombing by 
government forces hampered their advance but said they shot down five aircraft 
and killed more than 100 government soldiers. The government radio said the 
dead included four Americans, a Saudi national and some Pakistanis. Pakistan, 
the United States and Saudi Arabia back the guerrillas but deny having any 
nationals fighting in Afghanistan. 
