was removed Wednesday from a Cedar Street parking lot just east of 7th Avenue 
after being discovered by a passer-by. The San Diego Fire Department removed 
the bomb and detonated it after viewing X-rays of the device, above left. The 
incident was being treated as a random act. BOB GRIESER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031689-0050 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 31382 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 16, 1989, Thursday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 4; Column 1; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
