<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CONTRACT FOR TRAFFIC PROJECT OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Palos Verdes Estates City Council awarded a $22,512 contract Tuesday to 
Basmaciyan-Darnell Inc. of Costa Mesa to design Phase III of a troublesome 
intersection near Malaga Cove where Palos Verdes Drives West and North join. 
</P>
<P>
Phase III involves a stretch of Palos Verdes Drive West from Via Corta to the 
triangular intersection. The triangle itself and the curve sloping north to 
Torrance have already been designed. Construction on the curve will begin in 
the next few months, City Engineer Gary Wynn said. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Edward Ritscher, who cast the sole vote against awarding the 
contract, said BDI would favor signal lights at the intersection of Via Corta 
and Palos Verdes Drive West. Ritscher, like several other council members, 
opposes signals in the city. 
</P>
<P>
BDI said plans for the project will be completed in 32 weeks. 
