<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: SURGERY MAY END SEASON FOR CLU'S LEONHARDT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Leonhardt, a sophomore second baseman at Cal Lutheran and the team's 
leading hitter with a .390 average, underwent surgery on the middle finger of 
his right hand earlier this week and is expected to miss the rest of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Leonhardt broke his finger when he was hit on the hand by a line drive last 
week. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Brouelette will replace Leonhardt at second base. 
</P>
<P>
Former Pierce College outfielder Sebastian Goodlow has signed a free-agent 
contract with the Los Angeles Dodgers and will report to spring training in 
Vero Beach, Fla., on March 29. 
</P>
<P>
Goodlow, who attended Centennial High in Compton, batted .350 in 1987 and .279 
last season. 
</P>
<P>
Former Sylmar High standout Dana Ridenour was among 13 players sent Tuesday to 
the New York Yankees' minor league complex at Fort Lauderdale, Fla., for 
reassignment. 
</P>
<P>
Ridenour, 23, had been promoted to the Yankees' 40-man major league roster in 
November after spending three seasons in the team's farm system. 
</P>
<P>
Last season, Ridenour spent time with the Columbus (Ohio) Clippers of the 
triple-A International League and Albany-Colony (N.Y.) Yankees of the double-A 
Eastern League, compiling a 6-6 overall record with 14 saves. 
</P>
<P>
In 1987, Ridenour was named the Yankees' minor league pitcher of the year after 
posting a 5-4 record with a 1.77 earned-run average with the Ft. Lauderdale 
Yankees of the Class-A Florida State League. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus High will stage a basketball tournament next season on Dec. 1-5, and 
Coach John Clark is looking for teams. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley, Canyon and St. Genevieve are already scheduled, and Clark is 
hoping to attract as many as 14 teams. 
</P>
<P>
Rebecca Chiprut, 15, a student at Montclair Prep, finished second in the 
all-around class in a qualifying meet of the Southern California Gymnastics 
State Championships in the senior advanced optional division. 
</P>
<P>
Chiprut also placed second in the uneven bars and floor exercise and finished 
sixth on the balance beam. 
</P>
<P>
Angie Leonard, 11, of Sepulveda, won the vault, uneven bars and balance beam to 
claim the all-around title in a qualifying round in the advanced optional 
division for gymnasts aged 9-11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031689-0072 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 31434 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 16, 1989, Thursday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part 3; Page 17; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
306 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
5 HOME RUNS FUEL MASTER'S 13-7 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When the wind blows out at The Master's College baseball field, balls often do, 
too. 
</P>
<P>
In a nonleague game that featured six home runs, Master's outslugged Whittier, 
13-7, on the scoreboard and five to one in home runs on a gusty day at 
Master's. 
</P>
<P>
Mustangs' left fielder Darren Beck hit his first two home runs of the season 
and teammates Mark MacArthur, Dan Bevins and Scott Crowder each homered once. 
</P>
<P>
Master's senior right-hander Eric Petersen (2-0) went five innings and allowed 
four runs on four hits to pick up the win. 
</P>
<P>
He walked three and struck out two. 
</P>
<P>
Master's improved to 6-15-1. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cuesta 10, Pierce 4 -- Eileen Ramirez pitched a nine-hitter to stop host Pierce 
in a Western State Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
Agnes Florendo was two for three with three runs batted in for Cuesta (15-8, 
2-0). 
</P>
<P>
Andrea Federico, who went the distance for Pierce (5-14, 0-2), was three for 
three with an RBI. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 2, Ventura 0 -- Audra Olive hit a run-scoring triple in the fifth 
inning as Moorpark extended its Western State Conference winning streak to 15 
with a victory at Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
De Dow (11-3) threw a two-hitter and had nine strikeouts. She did not allow a 
runner to reach second base. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 5, Santa Monica 0 -- Michelle Ruffner pitched a two-hitter with five 
strikeouts and one walk in a Western State Conference game at Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
Ruffner (5-6) did not allow a runner past second base. 
</P>
<P>
Sherrie Holt, who was two for three, doubled to score Michele Wood for Canyons' 
first run in the second. 
</P>
<P>
Diana Franklin was two for four for Canyons (5-7, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Pierce d. Westmont, 15-6, 15-7, 15-11 -- Freshman middle blocker Tony Zapata 
had 13 kills and four stuff blocks to lead Pierce in a nonconference match at 
Westmont. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore middle blocker Mark Grondin also had four stuff blocks for Pierce 
(8-1). 
</P>
