<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Eagles national rugby team will split into two units and play a 
round-robin of scrimmages Sunday at UCLA with a Los Angeles all-star team. 
</P>
<P>
Afterward, one Eagle unit will leave for a World Sevens tournament in Australia 
and the other for a similar event in Hong Kong. Tommy Smith, formerly of UCLA, 
will captain the Australia-bound team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
