<P>
WELL-RESTED LAZERS FACE LEAGUE-LEADING BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having spent more than a week off after losing their fourth straight game, the 
Lazers will try to rebound tonight against the Baltimore Blast at 7:30 at the 
Forum. 
</P>
<P>
During their latest Major Indoor Soccer League tumble, the Lazers (16-19) have 
fallen eight games behind the first-place Blast. 
</P>
<P>
Baltimore (24-11), coming off a 4-3 overtime victory over the Tacoma Stars last 
Sunday, is 5 1/2 games ahead of its nearest challenger. 
</P>
