<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
JACKSON ASKS PROBE OF VIDEOTAPED ARREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rev. Jesse Jackson said Wednesday he has asked Atty. Gen. Dick Thornburgh 
to look into the Long Beach incident in which a white police officer was 
secretly videotaped as he appeared to push the head of black activist Don 
Jackson through a plate-glass window during his arrest for an alleged traffic 
violation in January. 
</P>
<P>
As a result of the phone conversation Tuesday with Jesse Jackson, Thornburgh 
has asked for a status report on the FBI investigation into the incident, a 
spokesman for the attorney general said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
