<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIET HAIRDRESSER WINS 'MISS AO DAI' CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BANGKOK, Thailand 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh City, formerly the old South Vietnamese capital of Saigon, held its 
first beauty contest since the 1975 Communist takeover, the state news agency 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Do Thi Khieu Khanh, a 20-year-old hairdresser, outshone 200 other women for the 
title "Miss Ao Dai 1989," the Vietnam News Agency said. 
</P>
<P>
Contestants modeled bathing suits, clothes of their own choice and ao dai -- 
tunics split to the waist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
