COUNCIL SEEKS TO FILL SEAT OF DEPARTING MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has accepted the resignation of Mayor William Davis and voted 
to accept applications from residents interested in being appointed to the City 
Council to fill the vacancy, according to Mayor Pro Tem John Kanel. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, 49, who announced his resignation in February, is moving to San 
Clemente. He has served on the City Council since 1986 and was a resident of 
Cypress for 16 years. 
</P>
