<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIFEGUARDS FIND BODY OF WOMAN IN LAGOON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lifeguards at Bolsa Chica State Beach on Wednesday found the body of a woman 
floating in an inland lagoon off Pacific Coast Highway near Warner Avenue, a 
spokesman for the Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified woman, believed to be in her 60s, weighed about 150 pounds and 
was about 5 feet 4 inches tall. She was fully clothed. The body was found about 
11:20 a.m. and showed no signs of trauma, Lt. Richard J. Olson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
