<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOUNDARIES TO SHIFT FOR ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pat Quinn, who led Saddleback High School into the Southern Section's 5-AA 
division title game, and Steve Keith, who led Irvine into the 5-A division 
title game, were named the boys' coaches for the Orange County All-Star 
basketball game June 25 in UC Irvine's Bren Center. 
</P>
<P>
Brad Pickler of Savanna and Stan DeMaggio of Capistrano Valley were named as 
coaches for the girls' game, which will be a preliminary to the boys' game. 
</P>
<P>
Pickler will coach the north girls' team after leading Savanna to a 
school-record 18 victories this season. DeMaggio will coach the south team. 
</P>
<P>
In the boys' game, Quinn will coach the north and Keith will coach the south 
under a revised format for selecting participants. 
</P>
<P>
The boundary for selecting coaches and members of the teams will be the Costa 
Mesa Freeway continuing north through Placentia and Yorba Linda. Schools on the 
west side of the freeway will designated as the north schools and the schools 
to the east will be designated as South schools. 
</P>
<P>
The north will be composed of 49 schools, including members of the Sunset 
League, Mater Dei, Santa Ana, Servite and Saddleback. The south will be 
composed of 25 schools, including members of the South Coast League, Corona del 
Mar and Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
Previously, the Garden Grove Freeway served as the dividing line for selecting 
the teams, but a recent shift in population in the Irvine, Mission Viejo and El 
Toro areas prompted the change. The North boys trail in the series, 13-10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ALL STAR TEAMS; BASKETBALL; HIGH SCHOOL ATHLETICS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031689-0132 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 31584 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 16, 1989, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
