WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
8 TEACHERS MAY BE LAID OFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Education agreed to notify eight probationary teachers that they 
may not be re-employed for the 1989-90 school year. 
</P>
<P>
The teachers, five from the high school and three from the middle schools, are 
on probationary status because they have been teaching in the district less 
than two years. 
</P>
<P>
Under the state education code, the district must notify teachers by March 15 
that they may be laid off during the next school year. The district will make a 
final decision on the layoffs after it is more certain about its budget. 
</P>
