<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
DMV OFFICE WILL REMAIN OPEN LATER IN AFTERNOONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The state Department of Motor Vehicles will extend the hours of its Long Beach 
office as part of a pilot program to make the office more convenient for 
motorists. 
</P>
<P>
Starting April 3, the office at 2627 Pacific Ave. will be open from 8 a.m. to 6 
p.m. weekdays except on Thursday, when it will be open until 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The office is one of only a few in the state participating in the program. 
Other offices in Long Beach and the Southeast will maintain their normal hours, 
a DMV spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
"With the extended hours program, we can be more responsive to our customers," 
DMV Director Del Pierce said in a prepared statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
