<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
GUN DEALER TO FACE TRIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Los Angeles gun dealer accused of the illegal sale of semiautomatic assault 
rifles will face trial in Pasadena Municipal Court May 1 after pleading 
innocent to the charges this week. 
</P>
<P>
The dealer, Ology Gibson, is accused of failing to obtain a Pasadena business 
license and a permit for an outdoor sale before selling assault rifles in the 
parking lot of a Pasadena gun store last month. 
</P>
<P>
He also is charged with three misdemeanor violations of the state Dangerous 
Weapons Control Act, including failure to observe a 15-day waiting period for 
concealed weapons. The city prosecutor's office contends that assault rifles 
are small enough to be concealed and therefore should require the same kind of 
waiting period imposed on handguns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
