<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
NEIGHBORS RALLY FOR LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of residents living near tiny Sunnyslope Library on Rosemead Boulevard 
have organized to fight to keep a library in their neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
The county has had a library in the Sunnyslope area for more than 75 years, but 
the current one-room facility may be demolished soon to make way for a 
mini-mall proposed by Arcadia developer Ron Rossiter. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Knicker, a leader of the residents' group, said they don't oppose the 
plan, but want a guarantee from the county that the Sunnyslope Library will be 
relocated. 
</P>
<P>
Linda Crismond, the county's chief librarian, said no decision has been made on 
the whether the library would be moved or closed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
