<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS AND GIRLS ALL-STAR HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL TEAMS TO BE ANNOUNCED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 1989 Times All-San Gabriel Valley boys and girls basketball teams will be 
announced in next Thursday's edition of the San Gabriel Valley section. 
</P>
<P>
The 10-player squads were selected by sportswriters based on a poll of coaches 
and discussions with scouts. Players will be honored at a breakfast and awards 
ceremony at 9 a.m. April 2 at the Anaheim Hilton, 777 Convention Way. 
</P>
<P>
All-stars from 12 Times circulation areas will be honored at the ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
Featured speaker will be George Yardley, an All-American basketball player at 
Stanford who starred in the National Basketball Assn. Yardley was the first 
player in NBA history to score more than 2,000 points in a season. 
</P>
