<DATELINE>
<P>
CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Discovery's astronauts took a long-distance call today from President Bush and 
set off a spectacular ice storm in space. 
</P>
<P>
Reviving a presidential space tradition that had lapsed since 1985, Bush 
praised shuttle commander Michael L. Coats and his crew as "today's pioneers," 
invited the Discovery astronauts and their families to visit the White House 
and pledged "to go forward with a strong, active space program." 
</P>
