<P>
FACTORY USE RATE DROPS TO 84.3% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The operating rate at U.S. factories, mines and utilities eased in February to 
84.3% of capacity, the first decline since last September, the government 
reported today. 
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve Board said February's operating rate dropped 0.2 percentage 
point from January's 84.5% level, a point that had not been surpassed in nearly 
a decade. 
</P>
<P>
The closer factories get to full capacity, the greater the fear they will have 
trouble producing enough goods to meet demand, leading to shortages and price 
increases. The Fed for a year has been nudging up interest rates in an effort 
to slow economic growth and thus restrain inflation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
